description:
Create a shared context object that extracted modules can use instead of closing over module-level variables.

## Problem
index.ts has ~15 module-level variables (state, orchestratorActive, worktreePool, sophiaCRResult, etc.) that all tool/command handlers close over. When we extract handlers into separate files, they need access to these.

## Solution
Define an OrchestratorContext interface in src/types.ts:

```typescript
export interface OrchestratorContext {
  state: OrchestratorState;
  pi: ExtensionAPI;
  orchestratorActive: boolean;
  worktreePool?: WorktreePool;
  sophiaCRResult?: PlanToCRResult;
  swarmTender?: SwarmTender;
  setPhase: (phase: OrchestratorPhase, ctx: ExtensionContext) => void;
  persistState: () => void;
  updateWidget: (ctx: ExtensionContext) => void;
  runHitMeAgents: (configs: {name:string,task:string}[], cwd: string, ctx: ExtensionContext) => Promise<HitMeResult>;
  agentMailRPC: (tool: string, args: Record<string,unknown>) => Promise<any>;
  ensureAgentMailProject: (cwd: string) => Promise<void>;
}
```

Create this interface and export it. Do NOT refactor index.ts yet — just define the contract.
Also export HitMeResult interface.

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] OrchestratorContext interface defined in src/types.ts
- [ ] HitMeResult interface exported
- [ ] npm run build passes
- [ ] npm test passes

